==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Posset
<hw>Pos"set</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W. <ets>posel</ets>
curdled milk, posset.]</ety> <def>A beverage composed of hot milk
curdled by some strong infusion, as by wine, etc., -- much in favor
formerly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I have drugged their <xex>posset</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Posset</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Posset
<hw>Pos"set</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Posseted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Posseting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To curdle; to turn,
as milk; to coagulate; <as>as, to <ex>posset</ex> the blood</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To treat with possets; to pamper.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧She was cosseted and
<xex>posseted</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>O. W. Holmes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Possibility</ent>⟦br⟧
